<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf64d35c0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s502"><num value="502">§ 502.</num><heading> Cargo exempt from forfeiture</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Cargo on a vessel is exempt from forfeiture under this title if—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf64d35c1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s502/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the cargo is owned in good faith by a person not the owner, master, or crewmember of the vessel; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf64d35c2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s502/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the customs duties on the cargo have been paid or secured for payment as provided by law.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf64d35c3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s4">Pub. L. 109–304, § 4</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1490">120 Stat. 1490</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
